1259
01:34:48,599 --> 01:34:51,434
Skeets, come on.
Give me that, you shithead.

1260
01:34:52,269 --> 01:34:53,603
Floyd, come on.

1261
01:34:59,026 --> 01:35:01,444
Will you throw that away, please?

1262
01:35:07,034 --> 01:35:08,785
Well, shit.

1263
01:35:21,465 --> 01:35:24,259
The kid passed. C-plus average.

1264
01:35:24,468 --> 01:35:26,553
Thought you'd like to know.

1265
01:35:42,778 --> 01:35:44,237
Warden wants to talk.

1266
01:35:58,002 --> 01:35:59,043
Out here?

1267
01:35:59,253 --> 01:36:01,504
That's what the man said.

1268
01:36:17,605 --> 01:36:18,855
Warden?

1269
01:36:28,616 --> 01:36:32,702
I'm asking you to keep this conversation
just between us.

1270
01:36:34,205 --> 01:36:36,456
I feel awkward enough as it is.

1271
01:36:54,892 --> 01:36:56,976
We got a situation here.

1272
01:36:57,853 --> 01:36:59,938
I think you can appreciate that.

1273
01:37:00,147 --> 01:37:01,397
Yes, sir.

1274
01:37:01,649 --> 01:37:03,066
I sure can.

1275
01:37:03,317 --> 01:37:07,362
I tell you, son, this thing really
came along and knocked my wind out.

1276
01:37:08,823 --> 01:37:11,407
It's got me up nights. That's the truth.

1277
01:37:13,661 --> 01:37:15,495
The right thing to do...

1278
01:37:17,164 --> 01:37:20,917
sometimes it's hard to know
what that is.

1279
01:37:21,919 --> 01:37:23,336
Do you understand?

1280
01:37:25,631 --> 01:37:27,257
I need your help, son.

1281
01:37:28,676 --> 01:37:30,844
If I'm going to move on this...

1282
01:37:31,178 --> 01:37:34,347
there can't be
the least little shred of doubt.

1283
01:37:35,099 --> 01:37:36,140
I have to know...

1284
01:37:36,308 --> 01:37:38,977
if what you told Dufresne
was the truth.

1285
01:37:39,186 --> 01:37:40,311
Yes, sir.

1286
01:37:40,521 --> 01:37:41,771
Absolutely.

1287
01:37:42,273 --> 01:37:45,275
Would you be willing to swear
before a judge and jury...

1288
01:37:45,442 --> 01:37:47,443
with your hand on the Good Book...

1289
01:37:47,653 --> 01:37:50,321
and take an oath
before Almighty God himself?

1290
01:37:50,531 --> 01:37:52,323
Just give me that chance.

1291
01:37:56,620 --> 01:37:57,954
That's what I thought.

1292
01:38:45,002 --> 01:38:46,920
I'm sure by now you've heard.

1293
01:38:48,672 --> 01:38:49,714
Terrible thing.

1294
01:38:51,342 --> 01:38:52,800
A man that young...

1295
01:38:53,135 --> 01:38:55,720
less than a year to go,
trying to escape.

1296
01:38:56,263 --> 01:38:58,765
Broke Captain Hadley's heart
to shoot him.

1297
01:38:59,516 --> 01:39:01,017
Truly, it did.

1298
01:39:04,021 --> 01:39:06,439
We just have to put it behind us.

1299
01:39:08,108 --> 01:39:09,359
Move on.

1300
01:39:10,945 --> 01:39:12,445
I'm done.

1301
01:39:13,739 --> 01:39:15,365
Everything stops.

1302
01:39:17,368 --> 01:39:19,702
Get someone else to run your scams.

1303
01:39:20,955 --> 01:39:22,789
Nothing stops.

1304
01:39:24,124 --> 01:39:25,500
Nothing.

1305
01:39:28,712 --> 01:39:31,798
Or you will do the hardest time there is.

1306
01:39:32,216 --> 01:39:34,550
No more protection from the guards.

1307
01:39:34,718 --> 01:39:39,639
I'll pull you out of that 1 -bunk Hilton
and cast you down with the sodomites.

1308
01:39:41,058 --> 01:39:43,476
You'll think you've been
fucked by a train.

1309
01:39:44,895 --> 01:39:46,396
And the library?

1310
01:39:47,064 --> 01:39:48,064
Gone.

1311
01:39:48,649 --> 01:39:51,234
Sealed off, brick by brick.

1312
01:39:51,694 --> 01:39:54,362
We'll have us a little
book barbecue in the yard.

1313
01:39:54,571 --> 01:39:56,698
They'll see the flames for miles.

1314
01:39:56,907 --> 01:39:59,742
We'll dance around it like wild lnjuns.

1315
01:40:00,995 --> 01:40:03,997
You understand me? Catching my drift?

1316
01:40:07,751 --> 01:40:09,585
Or am I being obtuse?

1317
01:40:21,390 --> 01:40:24,017
Give him another month
to think about it.

1318
01:41:10,773 --> 01:41:13,816
My wife used to say
I'm a hard man to know.

1319
01:41:14,651 --> 01:41:16,486
Like a closed book.

1320
01:41:17,279 --> 01:41:19,322
Complained about it all the time.

1321
01:41:20,240 --> 01:41:21,824
She was beautiful.

1322
01:41:24,203 --> 01:41:26,037
God, I loved her.

1323
01:41:29,458 --> 01:41:31,667
I didn't know how to show it, that's all.

1324
01:41:34,421 --> 01:41:36,089
I killed her, Red.

1325
01:41:37,966 --> 01:41:39,759
I didn't pull the trigger...

1326
01:41:41,178 --> 01:41:42,929
but I drove her away.

1327
01:41:44,431 --> 01:41:47,141
That's why she died, because of me...

1328
01:41:47,309 --> 01:41:48,684
the way I am.

1329
01:41:57,694 --> 01:41:59,529
That don't make you a murderer.

1330
01:42:02,908 --> 01:42:04,700
Bad husband, maybe.

1331
01:42:08,330 --> 01:42:11,582
Feel bad about it if you want,
but you didn't pull the trigger.

1332
01:42:11,792 --> 01:42:13,126
No, I didn't.

1333
01:42:13,544 --> 01:42:15,461
Somebody else did.

1334
01:42:16,713 --> 01:42:18,798
And I wound up in here.

1335
01:42:21,260 --> 01:42:22,885
Bad luck, I guess.

1336
01:42:28,058 --> 01:42:29,517
It floats around.

1337
01:42:30,561 --> 01:42:32,770
It's got to land on somebody.

1338
01:42:33,689 --> 01:42:35,565
It was my turn, that's all.

1339
01:42:36,275 --> 01:42:39,068
I was in the path of the tornado.

1340
01:42:44,992 --> 01:42:48,953
I just didn't expect the storm
would last as long as it has.

1341
01:42:53,292 --> 01:42:55,001
Think you'll ever get out of here?

1342
01:42:56,253 --> 01:42:57,670
Me?

1343
01:43:00,257 --> 01:43:01,591
Yeah.

1344
01:43:02,593 --> 01:43:04,886
One day, when I got
a long, white beard...

1345
01:43:05,095 --> 01:43:09,182
and two or three marbles rolling
around upstairs, they'll let me out.

1346
01:43:10,267 --> 01:43:11,934
I tell you where I'd go.

1347
01:43:13,395 --> 01:43:15,104
Zihuatanejo.

1348
01:43:15,939 --> 01:43:17,106
Say what?

1349
01:43:17,441 --> 01:43:19,275
Zihuatanejo.

1350
01:43:20,194 --> 01:43:21,861
It's in Mexico.

1351
01:43:23,238 --> 01:43:25,364
A little place on the Pacific Ocean.

1352
01:43:26,491 --> 01:43:29,285
You know what the Mexicans say
about the Pacific?

1353
01:43:31,121 --> 01:43:33,122
They say it has no memory.

1354
01:43:35,083 --> 01:43:37,752
That's where I want to live
the rest of my life.

1355
01:43:39,379 --> 01:43:41,881
A warm place with no memory.

1356
01:43:45,135 --> 01:43:47,053
Open up a little hotel...

1357
01:43:48,764 --> 01:43:50,264
right on the beach.

1358
01:43:50,849 --> 01:43:53,059
Buy some worthless old boat...

1359
01:43:53,602 --> 01:43:55,228
and fix it up new.

1360
01:43:57,981 --> 01:43:59,190
Take my guests out...

1361
01:44:00,025 --> 01:44:01,400
charter fishing.

1362
01:44:05,239 --> 01:44:06,989
Zihuatanejo.

1363
01:44:10,494 --> 01:44:14,372
In a place like that, I could use
a man that knows how to get things.

1364
01:44:20,921 --> 01:44:23,756
I don't think I could make it
on the outside.

1365
01:44:30,430 --> 01:44:32,515
I been in here most of my life.

1366
01:44:33,934 --> 01:44:35,685
I'm an institutional man now.

1367
01:44:36,603 --> 01:44:38,354
Just like Brooks was.

1368
01:44:39,815 --> 01:44:41,524
You underestimate yourself.

1369
01:44:42,067 --> 01:44:43,693
I don't think so.

1370
01:44:47,531 --> 01:44:51,450
In here I'm the guy who can get things
for you, sure, but...

1371
01:44:52,202 --> 01:44:54,745
outside all you need
is the Yellow Pages.

1372
01:44:54,955 --> 01:44:57,206
Hell, I wouldn't know
where to begin.

1373
01:44:59,334 --> 01:45:00,960
Pacific Ocean?

1374
01:45:01,378 --> 01:45:02,586
Shit.

1375
01:45:02,963 --> 01:45:05,172
Scare me to death, something that big.

1376
01:45:05,382 --> 01:45:06,674
Not me.

1377
01:45:07,884 --> 01:45:10,636
I didn't shoot my wife,
and I didn't shoot her lover.

1378
01:45:12,389 --> 01:45:15,599
Whatever mistakes I made,
I've paid for them and then some.

1379
01:45:16,643 --> 01:45:18,144
That hotel, that boat...

1380
01:45:19,896 --> 01:45:22,148
I don't think that's too much to ask.

1381
01:45:27,070 --> 01:45:29,488
You shouldn't be doing this to yourself.

1382
01:45:29,698 --> 01:45:31,741
This is just shitty pipe dreams.

1383
01:45:32,159 --> 01:45:34,618
Mexico is way down there
and you're in here...

1384
01:45:34,828 --> 01:45:36,412
and that's the way it is.

1385
01:45:36,747 --> 01:45:39,582
Yeah, right. That's the way it is.

1386
01:45:41,084 --> 01:45:43,461
It's down there and I'm in here.

1387
01:45:46,048 --> 01:45:48,758
I guess it comes down
to a simple choice.

1388
01:45:51,678 --> 01:45:53,179
Get busy living...

1389
01:45:54,556 --> 01:45:56,599
or get busy dying.

1390
01:46:08,695 --> 01:46:11,447
If you ever get out of here,
do me a favor.

1391
01:46:11,615 --> 01:46:13,908
Sure, Andy. Anything.

1392
01:46:15,786 --> 01:46:19,622
There's a big hayfield up near Buxton.
You know where Buxton is?

1393
01:46:21,124 --> 01:46:24,251
- A lot of hayfields up there.
- One in particular.

1394
01:46:24,461 --> 01:46:28,381
It's got a long rock wall
with a big oak tree at the north end.

1395
01:46:28,590 --> 01:46:31,467
It's like something
out of a Robert Frost poem.

1396
01:46:32,386 --> 01:46:34,887
It's where I asked my wife to marry me.

1397
01:46:36,306 --> 01:46:38,391
We went there for a picnic...

1398
01:46:38,809 --> 01:46:40,893
and made love under that oak...

1399
01:46:41,561 --> 01:46:43,813
and I asked and she said yes.

1400
01:46:47,818 --> 01:46:49,652
Promise me, Red.

1401
01:46:50,487 --> 01:46:53,823
If you ever get out...
find that spot.

1402
01:46:54,991 --> 01:46:59,829
At the base of that wall, there's a rock
that has no earthly business in Maine.

1403
01:47:00,956 --> 01:47:03,999
Piece of black, volcanic glass.

1404
01:47:06,670 --> 01:47:09,338
Something's buried under it
I want you to have.

1405
01:47:10,090 --> 01:47:11,340
What, Andy?

1406
01:47:11,758 --> 01:47:13,509
What's buried under there?

1407
01:47:15,095 --> 01:47:18,431
You'll have to pry it up...
to see.

1408
01:47:24,438 --> 01:47:26,272
No, I'm telling you. The guy is...

1409
01:47:26,940 --> 01:47:28,691
He's talking funny.

1410
01:47:29,776 --> 01:47:31,485
I'm really worried about him.

1411
01:47:31,862 --> 01:47:33,320
Let's keep an eye on him.

1412
01:47:33,530 --> 01:47:36,782
That's fine during the day,
but at night he's all alone.

1413
01:47:38,201 --> 01:47:39,368
Oh, Lord.

1414
01:47:40,704 --> 01:47:42,288
What?

1415
01:47:43,039 --> 01:47:45,791
Andy come down
to the loading dock today.

1416
01:47:46,001 --> 01:47:48,085
He asked me for a length of rope.

1417
01:47:48,295 --> 01:47:51,005
- Rope?
- Six feet long.

1418
01:47:51,214 --> 01:47:52,590
And you gave it to him.

1419
01:47:53,467 --> 01:47:55,259
Sure. Why wouldn't I?

1420
01:47:55,469 --> 01:47:57,052
Jesus! Heywood.

1421
01:47:57,637 --> 01:47:59,597
How was I supposed to know?

1422
01:47:59,806 --> 01:48:01,390
Remember Brooks Hatlen?

1423
01:48:03,393 --> 01:48:05,311
Andy would never do that.

1424
01:48:05,896 --> 01:48:07,354
Never.

1425
01:48:09,065 --> 01:48:10,399
I don't know.

1426
01:48:13,236 --> 01:48:15,237
Every man has his breaking point.

1427
01:48:17,574 --> 01:48:19,867
Lickety-split. Want to get home.

1428
01:48:20,160 --> 01:48:21,911
Just about finished, sir.

1429
01:48:39,054 --> 01:48:40,679
Three deposits tonight.

1430
01:48:48,647 --> 01:48:50,564
Get my stuff down to the laundry.

1431
01:48:50,774 --> 01:48:52,399
And shine my shoes.

1432
01:48:52,609 --> 01:48:55,528
- I want them looking like mirrors.
- Yes, sir.

1433
01:49:01,034 --> 01:49:02,493
It's good having you back.

1434
01:49:03,453 --> 01:49:05,287
Place wasn't the same without you.

1435
01:49:52,168 --> 01:49:53,544
Lights out!

1436
01:50:26,077 --> 01:50:28,621
I've had some long nights in the stir.

1437
01:50:29,164 --> 01:50:31,832
Alone in the dark
with nothing but your thoughts...

1438
01:50:32,042 --> 01:50:34,710
time can draw out like a blade.

1439
01:50:40,050 --> 01:50:43,052
That was the longest night of my life.

1440
01:50:58,902 --> 01:51:00,069
Give me a count!

1441
01:51:04,574 --> 01:51:07,409
Tier 3 south, clear!

1442
01:51:10,538 --> 01:51:13,707
Man missing on tier 2, cell 245!

1443
01:51:13,917 --> 01:51:14,958
Dufresne!

1444
01:51:15,502 --> 01:51:17,920
Come out. You're holding up the show!

1445
01:51:21,091 --> 01:51:24,468
Don't make me come down
or I'll thump your skull for you!

1446
01:51:32,060 --> 01:51:35,896
Damn it, you're putting me behind!
I got a schedule to keep.

1447
01:51:36,106 --> 01:51:39,400
You'd better be sick or dead in there.
I shit you not!

1448
01:51:39,609 --> 01:51:40,943
You hear me?

1449
01:51:47,033 --> 01:51:49,118
Oh, my Holy God.

1450
01:52:06,136 --> 01:52:08,679
I want every man
on this cellblock questioned.

1451
01:52:09,139 --> 01:52:11,682
- Start with that friend of his.
- Who?

1452
01:52:11,850 --> 01:52:13,267
Him.

1453
01:52:14,269 --> 01:52:15,811
Open 237.

1454
01:52:19,315 --> 01:52:22,985
What do you mean, "He just wasn't here"?
Don't say that to me.

1455
01:52:23,862 --> 01:52:26,447
- Don't say that to me again.
- But, sir, he wasn't.

1456
01:52:26,656 --> 01:52:30,159
I can see that, Haig! Think I'm blind?

1457
01:52:30,827 --> 01:52:32,411
Is that what you're saying?

1458
01:52:32,579 --> 01:52:35,080
- Am I blind, Haig?
- No, sir!

1459
01:52:35,999 --> 01:52:38,500
What about you. You blind?

1460
01:52:39,002 --> 01:52:41,545
- Tell me what this is.
- Last night's count.

1461
01:52:41,755 --> 01:52:45,048
You see Dufresne's name there?
I sure do. Right there.

1462
01:52:45,258 --> 01:52:46,592
"Dufresne."

1463
01:52:48,261 --> 01:52:51,013
He was in his cell at lights out.

1464
01:52:51,181 --> 01:52:54,099
Stands to reason he'd still be here
in the morning.

1465
01:52:54,434 --> 01:52:56,059
I want him found.

1466
01:52:56,269 --> 01:52:59,730
Not tomorrow, not after breakfast. Now!

1467
01:52:59,981 --> 01:53:01,190
Yes, sir.

1468
01:53:02,192 --> 01:53:05,986
Let's go. Move your butts. Move it!

1469
01:53:07,864 --> 01:53:08,864
Stand.

1470
01:53:10,283 --> 01:53:11,700
Well?

1471
01:53:14,788 --> 01:53:15,829
Well, what?

1472
01:53:15,997 --> 01:53:19,458
I see you two all the time.
You're thick as thieves, you are.

1473
01:53:20,543 --> 01:53:22,044
He must have said something.

1474
01:53:22,754 --> 01:53:25,672
No, sir, warden. Not a word.

1475
01:53:27,467 --> 01:53:30,052
Lord, it's a miracle!

1476
01:53:30,637 --> 01:53:33,222
Man vanished like a fart in the wind.

1477
01:53:33,890 --> 01:53:35,057
Nothing left...

1478
01:53:35,892 --> 01:53:38,602
but some damn rocks
on a windowsill.

1479
01:53:38,812 --> 01:53:41,563
And that cupcake on the wall.
Let's ask her.

1480
01:53:41,731 --> 01:53:43,524
Maybe she knows.

1481
01:53:43,733 --> 01:53:46,485
What say there, fuzzy-britches?
Feel like talking?

1482
01:53:47,904 --> 01:53:49,238
Guess not.

1483
01:53:49,781 --> 01:53:51,990
Why should she be any different?

1484
01:53:53,076 --> 01:53:54,743
This is a conspiracy.

1485
01:53:55,370 --> 01:53:57,079
That's what this is.

1486
01:53:57,789 --> 01:54:01,542
One big, damn conspiracy!

1487
01:54:01,793 --> 01:54:03,794
And everyone's in on it!

1488
01:54:04,420 --> 01:54:05,587
Including her!

1489
01:54:40,623 --> 01:54:44,960
In 1966... Andy
Dufresne escaped...

1490
01:54:45,128 --> 01:54:46,712
from Shawshank Prison.

1491
01:54:48,965 --> 01:54:51,508
All they found
was a muddy set of prison clothes...

1492
01:54:52,135 --> 01:54:55,470
a bar of soap... and
an old rock hammer...

1493
01:54:55,638 --> 01:54:58,140
damn near worn down to the nub.

1494
01:55:02,645 --> 01:55:07,399
I remember thinking it would take a man 600
years to tunnel through the wall with it.

1495
01:55:08,026 --> 01:55:10,652
Old Andy did it in less than 20.

1496
01:55:28,963 --> 01:55:31,256
Oh, Andy loved geology.

1497
01:55:32,008 --> 01:55:35,177
I imagine it appealed to
his meticulous nature.

1498
01:55:35,595 --> 01:55:37,429
An ice age here...

1499
01:55:37,847 --> 01:55:40,349
million years
of mountain-building there.

1500
01:55:41,351 --> 01:55:44,186
Geology is the study
of pressure and time.

1501
01:55:45,021 --> 01:55:47,022
That's all it takes, really.

1502
01:55:47,774 --> 01:55:49,066
Pressure...

1503
01:55:49,525 --> 01:55:51,026
and time.

1504
01:55:52,111 --> 01:55:54,196
That and a big goddamn poster.

1505
01:55:57,992 --> 01:55:59,159
Like I said...

1506
01:55:59,661 --> 01:56:03,664
in prison, a man will do anything
to keep his mind occupied.

1507
01:56:06,459 --> 01:56:11,254
Seems Andy's favorite hobby was toting
his wall out into the exercise yard...

1508
01:56:11,798 --> 01:56:13,715
a handful at a time.

1509
01:56:15,051 --> 01:56:17,094
I guess after Tommy was killed...

1510
01:56:17,303 --> 01:56:20,263
Andy decided
he'd been here long enough.

1511
01:56:20,473 --> 01:56:23,058
Lickety-split. I want to get home.

1512
01:56:23,768 --> 01:56:25,811
I'm just about finished, sir.

1513
01:56:47,250 --> 01:56:49,209
Three deposits tonight.

1514
01:56:56,509 --> 01:56:58,802
Andy did like he was told.

1515
01:56:59,012 --> 01:57:02,514
Buffed those shoes
to a high mirror-shine.

1516
01:57:06,185 --> 01:57:08,478
The guards simply didn't notice.

1517
01:57:08,771 --> 01:57:10,272
Neither did I.

1518
01:57:10,440 --> 01:57:11,982
I mean, seriously...

1519
01:57:12,191 --> 01:57:15,193
how often do you really look
at a man's shoes?

1520
01:59:18,734 --> 01:59:21,903
Andy crawled to freedom
through 500 yards...

1521
01:59:22,155 --> 01:59:25,490
of shit-smelling foulness
I can't even imagine.

1522
01:59:26,492 --> 01:59:28,827
Or maybe I just don't want to.

1523
01:59:33,249 --> 01:59:35,584
Five hundred yards.

1524
01:59:36,085 --> 01:59:39,171
That's the length
of five football fields.

1525
01:59:39,797 --> 01:59:42,382
Just shy of half a mile.

1526
02:00:37,605 --> 02:00:42,192
The next morning, right about the time
Raquel was spilling her secret...

1527
02:00:42,485 --> 02:00:45,320
a man nobody ever
laid eyes on before...

1528
02:00:45,571 --> 02:00:48,156
strolled into
the Maine National Bank.

1529
02:00:48,741 --> 02:00:51,910
Until that moment, he didn't exist.

1530
02:00:52,495 --> 02:00:54,829
- Except on paper.
- May I help you?

1531
02:00:55,248 --> 02:00:57,165
He had all the proper ID...

1532
02:00:57,375 --> 02:01:01,086
Driver's license, birth certificate,
Social Security card.

1533
02:01:01,504 --> 02:01:04,047
And the signature
was a spot-on match.

1534
02:01:04,257 --> 02:01:07,342
I must say I'm sorry
to be losing your business.

1535
02:01:07,551 --> 02:01:09,302
I hope you'll enjoy living abroad.

1536
02:01:10,096 --> 02:01:11,680
Thank you.

1537
02:01:11,847 --> 02:01:13,014
I'm sure I will.

1538
02:01:13,933 --> 02:01:17,269
Here's your cashier's check, sir.
Will there be anything else?

1539
02:01:17,478 --> 02:01:18,478
Please.

1540
02:01:19,021 --> 02:01:21,523
Would you add this
to your outgoing mail?

1541
02:01:22,024 --> 02:01:23,566
I'd be happy to.

1542
02:01:25,027 --> 02:01:26,361
Good day, sir.

1543
02:01:27,321 --> 02:01:31,741
Mr. Stevens visited nearly a dozen banks
in the Portland area that morning.

1544
02:01:32,201 --> 02:01:33,827
All told, he blew town...

1545
02:01:34,036 --> 02:01:38,873
with better than $370,000
of Warden Norton's money.

1546
02:01:39,542 --> 02:01:42,335
Severance pay for 19 years.

1547
02:01:49,552 --> 02:01:51,761
Good morning, Portland Daily Bugle.

1548
02:02:44,607 --> 02:02:47,567
Byron Hadley?
You have the right to remain silent.

1549
02:02:47,818 --> 02:02:52,280
If you give up this right, anything you
say can be held against you in court.

1550
02:02:52,698 --> 02:02:57,160
I wasn't there to see it, but I hear
Byron Hadley sobbed like a girl...

1551
02:02:57,370 --> 02:02:58,870
when they took him away.

1552
02:03:04,752 --> 02:03:08,129
Norton had no intention
of going that quietly.

1553
02:03:24,105 --> 02:03:25,480
Samuel Norton.

1554
02:03:25,648 --> 02:03:28,066
We have a warrant for your arrest.
Open up.

1555
02:03:32,822 --> 02:03:34,280
Open the door.

1556
02:03:34,448 --> 02:03:35,698
I'm not sure which key.

1557
02:03:45,835 --> 02:03:47,794
Make it easy on yourself, Norton!

1558
02:03:59,306 --> 02:04:02,767
I like to think the last thing
that went through his head...

1559
02:04:02,977 --> 02:04:04,561
other than that bullet...

1560
02:04:04,770 --> 02:04:09,190
was to wonder how the hell
Andy Dufresne ever got the best of him.

1561
02:04:11,694 --> 02:04:15,196
Not long after the warden
deprived us of his company...

1562
02:04:15,448 --> 02:04:17,532
I got a postcard in the mail.

1563
02:04:18,993 --> 02:04:21,828
It was blank, but the postmark said...

1564
02:04:22,037 --> 02:04:24,164
Fort Hancock, Texas.

1565
02:04:24,707 --> 02:04:26,040
Fort Hancock...

1566
02:04:26,333 --> 02:04:28,042
right on the border.

1567
02:04:28,461 --> 02:04:30,462
That's where Andy crossed.

1568
02:04:31,046 --> 02:04:35,175
When I picture him heading south
in his own car with the top down...

1569
02:04:35,509 --> 02:04:37,719
it always makes me laugh.

1570
02:04:39,555 --> 02:04:41,139
Andy Dufresne...

1571
02:04:41,515 --> 02:04:43,558
who crawled through
a river of shit...

1572
02:04:43,726 --> 02:04:46,144
and came out clean
on the other side.

1573
02:04:46,979 --> 02:04:48,354
Andy Dufresne...

1574
02:04:49,148 --> 02:04:50,732
headed for the Pacific.

1575
02:04:53,736 --> 02:04:55,904
Hadley's got him
by the throat, right?

1576
02:04:56,071 --> 02:04:59,908
He says, "I believe this boy's
about to have himself an accident."

1577
02:05:00,075 --> 02:05:02,952
Those of us who knew him best
talk about him often.

1578
02:05:03,621 --> 02:05:05,330
I swear, the stuff he pulled...

1579
02:05:05,539 --> 02:05:08,500
"My friends could use
a couple of beers."

1580
02:05:08,834 --> 02:05:10,502
And he got it!

1581
02:05:11,754 --> 02:05:14,130
Sometimes it makes me sad, though...

1582
02:05:14,423 --> 02:05:15,840
Andy being gone.

1583
02:05:16,550 --> 02:05:20,678
I have to remind myself that
some birds aren't meant to be caged.

1584
02:05:21,138 --> 02:05:23,223
Their feathers are just too bright.

1585
02:05:24,934 --> 02:05:26,643
And when they fly away...

1586
02:05:27,102 --> 02:05:31,481
the part of you that knows it was
a sin to lock them up does rejoice.

1587
02:05:32,566 --> 02:05:33,816
But still...

1588
02:05:34,276 --> 02:05:38,613
the place you live in is that much
more drab and empty that they're gone.

1589
02:05:42,826 --> 02:05:45,203
I guess I just miss my friend.

1590
02:06:09,645 --> 02:06:10,812
Please sit down.

1591
02:06:16,652 --> 02:06:18,236
Ellis Boyd Redding...

1592
02:06:18,779 --> 02:06:22,031
your files say you've served
40 years of a life sentence.

1593
02:06:22,825 --> 02:06:24,993
You feel you've been rehabilitated?

1594
02:06:26,829 --> 02:06:28,413
Rehabilitated?

1595
02:06:30,457 --> 02:06:32,333
Well, now, let me see.

1596
02:06:33,335 --> 02:06:35,670
I don't have any idea what that means.

1597
02:06:37,798 --> 02:06:40,049
It means you're ready
to rejoin society...

1598
02:06:40,634 --> 02:06:42,969
I know what you think it means, sonny.

1599
02:06:45,139 --> 02:06:47,140
To me it's just a made-up word.

1600
02:06:48,475 --> 02:06:50,810
A politician's word so that...

1601
02:06:51,228 --> 02:06:54,772
young fellas like yourself
can wear a suit and a tie...

1602
02:06:55,232 --> 02:06:56,858
and have a job.

1603
02:06:58,819 --> 02:07:00,903
What do you really want to know?

1604
02:07:01,697 --> 02:07:03,656
Am I sorry for what I did?

1605
02:07:04,074 --> 02:07:05,366
Well, are you?

1606
02:07:07,161 --> 02:07:09,996
There's not a day goes by
I don't feel regret.

1607
02:07:11,373 --> 02:07:14,834
Not because I'm in here
or because you think I should.

1608
02:07:18,297 --> 02:07:20,882
I look back on the way I was then...

1609
02:07:23,010 --> 02:07:24,344
a young...

1610
02:07:25,262 --> 02:07:28,765
stupid kid who committed
that terrible crime.

1611
02:07:31,769 --> 02:07:33,478
I want to talk to him.

1612
02:07:35,397 --> 02:07:37,899
I want to try
and talk some sense to him.

1613
02:07:38,609 --> 02:07:40,568
Tell him the way things are.

1614
02:07:42,655 --> 02:07:44,072
But I can't.

1615
02:07:46,283 --> 02:07:48,284
That kid's long gone...

1616
02:07:49,495 --> 02:07:52,246
and this old man is all that's left.

1617
02:07:53,666 --> 02:07:55,124
I got to live with that.

1618
02:07:56,502 --> 02:07:58,211
Rehabilitated?

1619
02:07:58,587 --> 02:08:00,421
It's just a bullshit word.

1620
02:08:01,340 --> 02:08:06,094
So you go on and stamp your forms,
sonny, and stop wasting my time.

1621
02:08:07,346 --> 02:08:09,597
Because to tell you the truth...

1622
02:08:09,932 --> 02:08:11,933
I don't give a shit.

1623
02:09:38,479 --> 02:09:39,854
Here you go, miss.

1624
02:09:42,816 --> 02:09:43,858
Restroom break?

1625
02:09:49,656 --> 02:09:54,202
You don't need to ask me every time you
need to go take a piss. Just go.

1626
02:09:55,204 --> 02:09:56,829
Yes, sir.

1627
02:10:07,216 --> 02:10:10,301
Forty years I've been asking
permission to piss.

1628
02:10:11,136 --> 02:10:14,138
I can't squeeze a drop without say-so.

1629
02:10:17,643 --> 02:10:19,811
There's a harsh truth to face.

1630
02:10:21,480 --> 02:10:24,398
No way I'm going to make it
on the outside.

1631
02:10:32,241 --> 02:10:35,952
All I do anymore is think of ways
to break my parole...

1632
02:10:36,745 --> 02:10:39,247
so maybe they'd send me back.

1633
02:10:44,419 --> 02:10:46,879
Terrible thing, to live in fear.

1634
02:10:47,756 --> 02:10:49,423
Brooks Hatlen knew it.

1635
02:10:49,633 --> 02:10:51,592
Knew it all too well.

1636
02:10:53,178 --> 02:10:56,597
All I want is to be back
where things make sense.

1637
02:10:57,015 --> 02:10:59,767
Where I won't have to be afraid
all the time.

1638
02:11:01,770 --> 02:11:04,105
Only one thing stops me.

1639
02:11:05,566 --> 02:11:07,942
A promise I made to Andy.

1640
02:11:28,463 --> 02:11:29,797
There it is.

1641
02:11:40,225 --> 02:11:41,893
Much obliged, sir.

1642
02:15:21,196 --> 02:15:22,488
Dear Red:

1643
02:15:22,697 --> 02:15:25,199
If you're reading this,
you've gotten out...

1644
02:15:25,367 --> 02:15:29,537
and if you've come this far,
maybe you're willing to come a bit further.

1645
02:15:29,704 --> 02:15:32,206
You remember the name
of the town, don't you?

1646
02:15:34,501 --> 02:15:36,001
Zihuatanejo.

1647
02:15:37,629 --> 02:15:41,215
I could use a good man
to help me get my project on wheels.

1648
02:15:41,716 --> 02:15:45,261
I'll keep an eye out for you,
and the chessboard ready.

1649
02:15:46,054 --> 02:15:47,471
Remember, Red...

1650
02:15:47,806 --> 02:15:49,890
hope is a good thing...

1651
02:15:50,100 --> 02:15:52,101
maybe the best of things.

1652
02:15:52,310 --> 02:15:54,478
And no good thing ever dies.

1653
02:15:55,021 --> 02:15:57,898
I will be hoping
that this letter finds you...

1654
02:15:58,066 --> 02:15:59,817
and finds you well.

1655
02:16:00,318 --> 02:16:02,903
Your friend... Andy.

1656
02:16:36,771 --> 02:16:40,608
"Get busy living...
or get busy dying."

1657
02:16:43,278 --> 02:16:45,446
That's goddamn right.

1658
02:16:50,702 --> 02:16:52,828
For the second time in my life...

1659
02:16:53,079 --> 02:16:55,623
I'm guilty of committing a crime.

1660
02:16:56,708 --> 02:16:58,626
Parole violation.

1661
02:16:59,294 --> 02:17:02,963
Of course, I doubt they'll toss up
any roadblocks for that.

1662
02:17:03,632 --> 02:17:05,674
Not for an old crook like me.

1663
02:17:05,884 --> 02:17:07,927
Fort Hancock, Texas, please.

1664
02:17:11,598 --> 02:17:16,310
I find I'm so excited I can barely
sit still or hold a thought in my head.

1665
02:17:16,770 --> 02:17:20,105
I think it's the excitement
only a free man can feel.

1666
02:17:20,315 --> 02:17:22,816
A free man at the start
of a long journey...

1667
02:17:22,984 --> 02:17:25,611
whose conclusion is uncertain.

1668
02:17:28,615 --> 02:17:31,283
I hope I can make it across the border.

1669
02:17:32,786 --> 02:17:35,829
I hope to see my friend
and shake his hand.

1670
02:17:37,666 --> 02:17:41,752
I hope the Pacific is as blue
as it has been in my dreams.

1671
02:17:43,588 --> 02:17:44,797
I hope.

